Ah, okay.

261
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:09,433
Okay.

262
00:17:09,567 --> 00:17:11,300
Good.

263
00:17:11,433 --> 00:17:12,967
Let's eat.

264
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:15,400
- You're just having salad?
- I'm on a diet.

265
00:17:16,233 --> 00:17:17,367
Okay.

266
00:17:17,500 --> 00:17:18,633
Okay.

267
00:17:20,133 --> 00:17:21,100
Jun,

268
00:17:22,700 --> 00:17:24,667
why can't I contact you?

269
00:17:28,600 --> 00:17:31,167
Dad, are you okay?

270
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:34,733
Glen, yeah, I'm okay.

271
00:17:34,867 --> 00:17:36,067
Are you sure?

272
00:17:37,833 --> 00:17:39,733
It's like you saw a ghost.

273
00:17:57,067 --> 00:18:00,267
Sir Dante, what's the news?

274
00:18:00,567 --> 00:18:01,467
I just want to know

275
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:04,100
if your girlfriend knows
anything about our boss.

276
00:18:04,333 --> 00:18:05,267
She doesn't know anything.

277
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:10,633
Sir, I'm going to be transferred
to Calabari State Prison.

278
00:18:10,900 --> 00:18:12,533
I'll rot there.

279
00:18:12,667 --> 00:18:15,767
If I don't get out of there,
I'll start talking.

280
00:18:16,333 --> 00:18:19,800
Your business and your boss's
reputation will collapse.

281
00:18:19,933 --> 00:18:22,167
Okay, I'll talk to Sir.

282
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,933
You shouldn't make it to where
they are transferring you.

283
00:18:32,067 --> 00:18:32,700
Faye...

284
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:35,600
Why are you still here?

285
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:38,600
I waited for you because maybe
no one would take Miss Faye.

286
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:41,267
Ah, no, I'll take her.

287
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:43,267
Oh, no, I have a driver.

288
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:45,833
Ah, Jhem is your friend.

289
00:18:46,100 --> 00:18:46,867
Yes.

290
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:49,467
It's sad that she just
fell in love,

291
00:18:49,600 --> 00:18:51,433
and then that's what happened
to her.

292
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:54,700
By the way, thank you earlier.

293
00:18:56,133 --> 00:18:58,600
You know,
what she said was right.

294
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:01,800
If you choose your boyfriend,
he should be strong.

295
00:19:02,933 --> 00:19:04,900
One who has been there for you
for a long time.

296
00:19:05,933 --> 00:19:07,367
Actually,

297
00:19:07,700 --> 00:19:09,300
it's not an assurance that
you've known someone

298
00:19:09,433 --> 00:19:10,533
for a long time.

299
00:19:10,933 --> 00:19:15,433
Sometimes, people you just
met are better,

300
00:19:15,800 --> 00:19:20,633
especially if they're smart,
handsome, and above all,

301
00:19:20,767 --> 00:19:22,200
in a good status in life.

302
00:19:26,167 --> 00:19:29,100
Guys, you both have a point,

303
00:19:29,267 --> 00:19:32,000
but that's not
on my mind right now.

304
00:19:32,133 --> 00:19:35,567
Besides, it's important for me
that my dad approves of him.

305
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:43,667
Guys, my driver is here.

306
00:19:43,800 --> 00:19:45,233
Thanks again.

307
00:19:45,367 --> 00:19:49,667
I also want to invite you
to my dad's Luau party.

308
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,767
Allan, if you're free,
come too.

309
00:19:51,900 --> 00:19:53,433
Sure, I'm free.

310
00:19:53,567 --> 00:19:55,467
Okay, thank you. Bye!

311
00:19:55,600 --> 00:19:56,767
I'll walk you.

312
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:20,067
- Okay, Vince,
- You know...

313
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:20,867
I'll go first, okay?

314
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,200
Take care.

315
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:38,367
You seem stressed out, Dad.

316
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:40,133
Of course.

317
00:20:40,267 --> 00:20:41,700
I'm the Mayor.

318
00:20:42,800 --> 00:20:48,167
All mayors have their own
problems, like the fugitive.

319
00:20:48,300 --> 00:20:51,333
The one fugitive hasn't been
caught yet.

320
00:20:51,467 --> 00:20:52,467
I thought you were stressed

321
00:20:52,600 --> 00:20:55,333
because of what you were talking
about on the phone.

322
00:20:55,467 --> 00:20:56,333
Who was that?

323
00:20:57,267 --> 00:20:58,467
It's Bobby.

324
00:20:59,933 --> 00:21:01,733
I'm worried for her.

325
00:21:01,867 --> 00:21:04,767
Maybe she's still looking
for the fugitive.

326
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:07,000
Are you sure it's Bobby
you're talking to?

327
00:21:07,500 --> 00:21:08,533
Let me see.

328
00:21:10,333 --> 00:21:11,000
What?

329
00:21:12,667 --> 00:21:13,933
Just kidding, Dad.

330
00:21:14,067 --> 00:21:16,933
I just did what you did
to me earlier, remember?

331
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,167
Of course, I trust you.

332
00:21:19,300 --> 00:21:21,400
I know you're telling the truth,

333
00:21:22,933 --> 00:21:25,033
unless you're hiding something
from me.

334
00:21:26,400 --> 00:21:28,300
We all have something to hide,

335
00:21:29,667 --> 00:21:30,633
a secret.

336
00:21:32,667 --> 00:21:33,667
Right, Son?

337
00:22:01,067 --> 00:22:05,567
Bring your grandmother with you,
and her two bodyguards.

338
00:22:06,700 --> 00:22:07,700
Thank you, Mayor.

339
00:22:08,367 --> 00:22:13,333
Tomorrow, maybe only grandmother
will be there.

340
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,100
I have a duty tomorrow.

341
00:22:16,267 --> 00:22:18,333
I'll ask permission from Major.

342
00:22:18,467 --> 00:22:20,567
Oh, no, Mayor, no need.

343
00:22:20,700 --> 00:22:22,633
I don't want special treatment.

344
00:22:24,667 --> 00:22:27,067
Okay, I'll fix my schedule.

345
00:22:28,633 --> 00:22:29,667
Mayor...

346
00:22:31,433 --> 00:22:34,167
How about Ma'am Sophia?

347
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:36,967
That's okay.
She'll give in to me.

348
00:22:37,100 --> 00:22:40,000
It's my day after all.
I'm sure she'll agree.

349
00:22:40,133 --> 00:22:42,200
But, just in case,

350
00:22:43,867 --> 00:22:47,100
I'll ask her to get mad at me
some other time.

351
00:22:54,633 --> 00:22:56,167
Bobby, by the way.

352
00:22:56,767 --> 00:22:58,867
I want to ask for your help.

353
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:03,567
My friend, Jun Alferez.

354
00:23:04,133 --> 00:23:06,267
He's been missing
since yesterday.

355
00:23:06,767 --> 00:23:09,633
He was on his motorbike
yesterday, but until now.

356
00:23:09,767 --> 00:23:10,967
I haven't been able
to contact him.

357
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:13,833
Did you find out his last
possible location?

358
00:23:14,867 --> 00:23:16,767
Does he have enemies?

359
00:23:17,800 --> 00:23:19,733
What was his purpose
before he disappeared?

360
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,200
<i> Follow Glen.</i>

361
00:23:22,367 --> 00:23:29,200
<i>I just want to know
if my son is human or a demon.</i>

362
00:23:46,367 --> 00:23:47,300
Monty called.

363
00:23:47,433 --> 00:23:49,200
He said if we don't
help him escape,

364
00:23:49,333 --> 00:23:51,067
he'll expose and implicate you.

365
00:23:51,200 --> 00:23:51,967
What's your plan, Boss?

366
00:23:52,100 --> 00:23:53,433
What? Are you and Enriquez
together?

367
00:23:53,567 --> 00:23:54,600
Work on that first.

368
00:23:54,733 --> 00:23:55,600
Get down!

369
00:23:55,767 --> 00:23:57,033
They're so ugly!

370
00:23:57,167 --> 00:23:58,333
Send them away.

371
00:23:58,467 --> 00:24:01,600
You're like starving,
ugly people.

372
00:24:01,733 --> 00:24:03,433
You even got ahead
of the guests.

373
00:24:03,567 --> 00:24:07,867
I can accept
that we are starving.

374
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,200
But to call us ugly...

375
00:24:10,333 --> 00:24:12,167
You're already offending us.

376
00:24:12,300 --> 00:24:14,067
I'll punish you.

377
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,300
- Deserve.
- No!

378
00:24:16,833 --> 00:24:20,367
I wish you and Faye
were the only children I have.

379
00:24:20,500 --> 00:24:22,567
What's with you?
Why are you saying that?

380
00:24:22,700 --> 00:24:25,600
Don't make the mistake letting
Monty escape again, okay?

381
00:24:25,733 --> 00:24:28,433
If the police catch him,
we'll all be in trouble.
